sql:
SELECT airport_name
FROM airports
WHERE terminal_count = (SELECT MAX(terminal_count) FROM airports);

external_knowledge:
- This query assumes that the total fare paid for a booking is equivalent to the fare of the flight; 
- The query does not account for any potential fare differences for different passengers on the same flight; 
- The query is designed to handle a scenario where a flight may not have any bookings.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT p.name
FROM passengers p
JOIN bookings b ON p.passenger_id = b.passenger_id;

SELECT COUNT(flight_id) AS active_flight_count
FROM flight_schedules
WHERE status = 'active';
